x4freetext: 2 boron counters - for neutron beam monitoring.
Measurement with graphite sample was used to define
incident neutron energy and for normalizetion;
used values are not given in articles.
.Boundary condition for the wave function on the
.Boundary condition for the wave function on the
R-matrix formalism of Lein and Thomas
Scattered neutron spectra were measured at
angles of 45, 90, 135 degrees, with and without sample.
After summing in wide intervals, normalization to
monitor counting and corrections, three spectra of
scattered neutron intensities were approximated by
Legendre polynomials, there sets of parameters
( Legendre coefficients and c-s) were defined; the
last ( at 135 degrees) set was defined relative to
For detector efficiency dependence from scattering
ERR-ANALYS was corrected. BIB information was added.
Several misprints in data values were corrected
according to Table 1. ERR-S -> DATA-ERR (not specified)
Details of method was added from REL-REF of V.A.Vagov+
